    "title": "Can't minimize BitcoinQt to tray",
    "body": "<!-- Describe the issue -->\r\nI've upgraded to BitcoinQt 0.16.1 and now I can't minimize to tray.\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\nCheck the setting and it work.\r\n\r\n### Reproducing\r\nI don't really know if this is a problem with gnome in Ubuntu 18.04.1 LTS, but this is an almost clean installation (reinstalled +- 1w ago).\r\nI downloaded the compiled binary from https://bitcoin.org/en/download and verified the signature/hash.\r\nInstalled following the steps given in the webpage.\r\nTried to mark the Window options to minimize to tray, but It only works once.\r\nAfter you open the window it doesn't minimize to tray again, even with the settings checked.\r\n\r\n### My machine infos\r\n```bash\r\njohnny ~ uname -a\r\nLinux mars 4.15.0-29-generic #31-Ubuntu SMP Tue Jul 17 15:39:52 UTC 2018 x86_64 x86_64 x86_64 GNU/Linux\r\njohnny ~ cat /etc/issue\r\nUbuntu 18.04.1 LTS \\n \\l\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Logs & images\r\nEvery time I restart it appears unchecked.\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/14189387/43286925-cac0ef88-90f9-11e8-93e0-51eabcfb8970.png)\r\n\r\n[debug.log](https://pastebin.com/raw/3AWvpGXw)\r\n[bitcoin.config w/o rpc](https://pastebin.com/raw/gyGXj7GN)\r\n",
